<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container content-narrow">
    <h2>What Original Medicare Doesn&rsquo;t Cover</h2>
    <p>Many people are surprised to learn that Original Medicare (Parts A and B) doesn&rsquo;t cover most of what we think of as &ldquo;everyday&rdquo; healthcare:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Routine dental cleanings, fillings, crowns, dentures</li>
      <li>Routine eye exams, glasses, or contact lenses</li>
      <li>Hearing exams or hearing aids</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The good news: there are several ways to add this coverage.</p>

    <h2>Option 1: Medicare Advantage Plans</h2>
    <p>Most <a href="medicare-advantage.html">Medicare Advantage</a> plans include dental, vision, and hearing benefits at no extra premium. Coverage levels vary by plan &mdash; some include only cleanings and exams, while others cover crowns, dentures, and hearing aids with meaningful allowances.</p>
    <p>If dental, vision, and hearing are important to you, this is often the simplest path.</p>

    <h2>Option 2: Standalone Dental, Vision &amp; Hearing Plans</h2>
    <p>Available alongside Original Medicare and Medicare Supplement plans. These let you keep the doctor flexibility of Original Medicare/Supplement while adding ancillary coverage. Premiums and benefits vary widely.</p>

    <h2>Option 3: Discount Programs</h2>
    <p>Some dental and vision discount programs aren&rsquo;t insurance, but offer reduced rates at participating providers. Useful for occasional needs without committing to a full insurance premium.</p>

    <h2>What to Look For</h2>
    <p>When comparing dental, vision, and hearing benefits:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Annual maximums</strong> &mdash; how much will the plan pay per year?</li>
      <li><strong>Waiting periods</strong> &mdash; can you use major benefits right away, or do you have to wait?</li>
      <li><strong>Network</strong> &mdash; is your dentist or audiologist included?</li>
      <li><strong>Hearing aid allowances</strong> &mdash; some plans offer $1,000+, others much less</li>
      <li><strong>Vision allowances</strong> &mdash; how much toward frames and lenses each year?</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Let&rsquo;s find the right fit.</strong>
      <p style="margin:8px 0 0;">If dental work, hearing aids, or eye care matter to you, tell us &mdash; we&rsquo;ll help you compare plans where these benefits actually shine. Some plans have great dental but minimal hearing; others are the reverse. The right choice depends on what you actually need.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

